subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. This is one of the species with the elytra nearly as wide as long, and wide elytral epipleura easily visible from above (
Fig. 60
); frons widely, shallowly grooved, with rather long, white pubescence; pronotum strongly convex with indistinct lateroposterior depressions and short, white pubescence; antennae extremely short, scarcely reaching the anterior pronotal quarter when laid alongside the prontum; aedeagus short and very robust, with small preapical spines (
Fig. 77
).
